found Dagada to have been involved in price fixing with a service provider to
the City, and in the process acted against his sworn duty to our residents,”
Mashaba said.“It is understood from the
investigation that Cllr Dagada has acted in a manner which has sought, either
directly or indirectly, to benefit service providers and officials closely
associated with him.“ In this process a series of
events have transpired that, in my view, could not have taken place
